{
  "id": "L03",
  "title": "Just One Stroopwafel",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Welcome to the Albert Cuypmarkt in Amsterdam! Today, you'll learn how to buy one of the most famous Dutch treats: a fresh, warm stroopwafel."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L03_V01",
      "data": {
        "De stroopwafel": "The stroopwafel"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L03_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "Stroopwafel",
        "phonetic": "st-ROHP-wah-full",
        "tip": "The 'oo' in 'stroop' is a long 'o' sound, like in the word 'hope'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L03_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Goedemorgen",
        "meaning": "Good morning"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L03_V02",
      "data": {
        "Eén": "One"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L03_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Alstublieft",
        "meaning": "Please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "'Alstublieft' is a magic word in Dutch. You use it when you ask for something, like 'please'."
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L03_S01",
      "title": "Place Your Order",
      "setting": "You are at a stroopwafel stall at the Albert Cuypmarkt. It's time to get the vendor's attention and order.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Greet the vendor"
        },
        {
          "title": "Order one stroopwafel",
          "chatbot_message": "Goedemorgen!"
        },
        {
          "title": "Wait for your order",
          "chatbot_message": "Oké. Eén stroopwafel."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L03_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Wat kost dat?",
        "meaning": "What does that cost?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L03_V03",
      "data": {
        "Dat": "That"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L03_V04",
      "data": {
        "is": "is"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L03_V05",
      "data": {
        "Twee": "Two"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L03_V06",
      "data": {
        "De euro": "The euro"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L03_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "euro",
        "phonetic": "EU-roh",
        "tip": "The 'eu' sound is unique to Dutch. It's similar to the 'ea' in 'earn' but with more rounded lips."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L03_V07",
      "data": {
        "Contant": "Cash (payment)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Remember the magic word 'Alstublieft'? You also use it when you give something to someone. It means 'Here you are'."
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L03_S02",
      "title": "Confirm and Pay",
      "setting": "The vendor has prepared your warm stroopwafel and is holding it out for you.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Ask for the price",
          "chatbot_message": "Alstublieft."
        },
        {
          "title": "Say you will pay with cash",
          "chatbot_message": "Dat is twee euro."
        },
        {
          "title": "Hand over the money and say 'please'",
          "chatbot_message": "Prima."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L03_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dank je",
        "meaning": "Thank you"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L03_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dank je wel",
        "meaning": "Thank you very much"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Both 'Dank je' and 'Dank je wel' mean 'thank you'. 'Dank je wel' is a bit stronger and more polite."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L03_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Eet smakelijk",
        "meaning": "Enjoy your meal"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L03_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dag",
        "meaning": "Bye"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L03_P03",
      "data": {
        "word": "Dag",
        "phonetic": "Dakh",
        "tip": "The 'g' at the end of 'dag' is a soft, scraping sound made in the back of your throat. It is a typical Dutch sound."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L03_S03",
      "title": "Receive and Depart",
      "setting": "You've paid and have your delicious stroopwafel. Time to thank the vendor and leave.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Say 'thank you very much'",
          "chatbot_message": "Dank je."
        },
        {
          "title": "Say goodbye",
          "chatbot_message": "Eet smakelijk!"
        },
        {
          "title": "Enjoy your stroopwafel!",
          "chatbot_message": "Dag!"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}